        "commitchunkandadvancecontext"
      ],
      "depth": 1,
      "type_signature": "(ppg_clean: array-like or tensor, noise: array-like or tensor, sampling_rate: int or float, generator: callable model (e.g., torch.nn.Module), device: device specifier (string or torch.device)) -> tensor or array-like",
      "matched_primitive": null,
      "is_optional": false,
      "is_opaque": false,
      "is_external": false,
      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "Conditional Latent-to-Sequence Generator. This operation applies a learned parametric mapping that takes two inputs: a structured context tensor and a latent noise tensor. It outputs a synthesized sequence/tensor sampled from a learned conditional distribution, where the context enforces structural consistency and the latent input controls variation. With fixed model weights and fixed latent input, the mapping is deterministic; varying the latent input produces alternative plausible realizations.. Applications: Reconstructing corrupted segments in multivariate industrial telemetry conditioned on clean context windows., Generating synthetic seismic or acoustic traces conditioned on local baseline measurements for simulation and augmentation., Producing alternative robotic actuator trajectories conditioned on nominal motion context for robustness testing., Creating plausible physiological or environmental waveform variants conditioned on a reference segment for data augmentation.",
      "critic_notes": "",
      "decomposition_rationale": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": "initializereconstructionbudget",
      "parent_id": "generatereconstructedppg",
      "name": "InitializeReconstructionBudget",
